Found how to fix the tests: this is the why of the "methods" object.

Add the "performance" object to the "methods":

```typescript

const methods: any = {
  // snip...
  Date,
  performance,
  // snip...
}
```

And use it in `getTimestamp`:
```typescript
function getTimestamp(): number {
  return methods.performance.now()
}
```

In the unit tests, we are installing sinonjs/fake-timers with that "methods" object. Adding the "performance" entry in it, sinonjs/fake-timer will found it and replace it with its fake one

